nus, \"When Did \"the '60s\" Begin? A Cautionary Tale for Historians\" 4 Feb 2014, History News Network]\n* [https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/americanexperience/films/1964/  \"1964\" (PBS documentary, 2013)]\n* {{cite news|last1=Zurawik|first1=David|title=On PBS, Six Hours of The '60s|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/1991-01-20/features/1991020182_1_boomers-sixties-obsession|accessdate=22 September 2015|work=The Baltimore Sun Times|date=20 January 1991}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|1960s}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* [http://www.public.iastate.edu/~rjackson/webbibl.html The 1960s: A Bibliography]\n* [http://archives.cbc.ca/IDD-1-69-1587/life_society/60s/ CBC Digital Archives{{spaced ndash}} 1960s a GoGo]\n* [http://www3.iath.virginia.edu/sixties/ The Sixties Project]\n* [http://www.life.com/image/first/in-gallery/56281/heroes-of-the-1960s#index/0 Heroes of the 1960s]{{spaced ndash}} slideshow by ''[[Life magazine]]''\n* [http://www.lib.virginia.edu/small/exhibits/sixties/ The 60s: Literary Tradition and Social Change], exhibit at the [[University of Virginia]], Library, Special Collections.\n* [http://www.klarbooks.com/academic/protest.html 1960s protest movements in America]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080724092323/http://www.1968ineurope.com/ The 1960s in Europe (Online Teaching and Research Guide)]\n* {{cite web  |publisher= [[Victoria and Albert Museum]]  |url= http://www.vam.ac.uk/collections/fashion/features/1960s/index.html  |title= 1960s Fashion Feature, including biographies, interviews, clothing and resources  |url-status= dead  |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080509050501/http://www.vam.ac.uk/collections/fashion/features/1960s/index.html  |archivedate= 9 May 2008  |df= dmy-all  }}\n* [http://www.history.com/topics/1960s The 1960s]{{spaced ndash}} articles, video, pictures, and facts\n* [http://www.sixtiespix.com/  A 1960s photographic archive]\n\n{{Events by month links}}\n{{20th century}}\n\n[[Category:1960s| ]]\n[[Category:20th century]